1) Instalation of required software packets on Ubuntu 12.04:

sudo apt-get install cython libboost-all-dev libboost-python-dev \
                     libboost-signals-dev libboost-thread-dev\
                     libboost-filesystem-dev libboost-system-dev \
                     libboost-iostreams-dev python-gnuplot gnuplot \
                     gnuplot-x11  python-scipy python-sciscipy python-numpy \
                     python-matplotlib

2) Building python bindings

make

3) Testing the chip

./do.py chipname





4) To enable efuse burning you have to:

!! WARNING: I2C address of current monitor is different than on NIKHEF board !!
  
a) build SpidrTpx3Lib with different flags:
   cd spidr/software/trunk
   qmake SPIDR-TPX3-PROBESTATION.pro
   make
b) build python binding
   cd spidr/software/trunk/python
   make CERN_PROBESTATION=1
c) to read efuses you can:
   ./tpx3_tests.py chipname test17_efuse
d) to write efuses you can:
   ./tpx3_tests.py chipname "test17_efuse(name='W0_J4')"
   



5) Changing linux UDP buffers:
  sudo sysctl -w net.core.rmem_max=33554432
  sudo sysctl -w net.core.rmem_default=33554432
